      "patchset_number": 6,
      "line": 53,
      "message": "Sure.In the parseURL(), if the version is not passed in the URL, the matcher condition will fail which will return in null idUrl object. If the idUrl is null, it will be returned back. So version will always be not-null at \"if(version ==null)\". Doing a null check for the object which will never be null is redundant that's why I have removed it. The same explanation applies for the rest of the lines.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 3813,
        "name": "Lathishbabu Ganesan",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "lathishbabu.ganesan@est.tech",
